  <div class="container">
    <header>
      <div class="logo">SA</div>
      <div>
        <h1>Swipies AI Telegram Bot</h1>
        <p class="lead">Simple Telegram bot that connects <span class="accent">Swipies AI (RAGFlow)</span> with Telegram using <span class="badge">aiogram</span> and <span class="badge">httpx</span>.</p>
      </div>
    </header>

    <main>
      <section class="card">
        <h2>‚ú® What it does</h2>
        <p class="muted">This project forwards messages from Telegram users to a Swipies AI chat completion endpoint and returns the generated response back to the chat. It's asynchronous and minimal ‚Äî perfect as a starting point for more advanced integrations.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="card">
        <h2>‚ú® Features</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Connects Telegram bot ‚Üí Swipies AI (RAGFlow)</li>
          <li>Sends user messages to the Swipies AI chat completion API</li>
          <li>Parses streaming-like <code>data:</code> chunks and reconstructs final text</li>
          <li>Shows ‚Äútyping‚Ä¶‚Äù status while generating</li>
          <li>Fully asynchronous using <code>aiogram</code> and <code>httpx</code></li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="card">
        <h2>üìå Requirements</h2>
        <p class="small">Make sure you have Python 3.10+ and the required packages installed.</p>
        <pre><code>pip install aiogram httpx</code></pre>
      </section>

      <section class="card">
        <h2>üìÅ Project Structure</h2>
        <p class="muted">Everything is inside one file for simplicity:</p>
        <pre><code>main.py</code></pre>
      </section>

      <section class="card">
        <h2>üîß Environment Variables</h2>
        <p class="muted">Before running, fill these fields in the script or ‚Äî better ‚Äî read them from a <code>.env</code> file / environment variables:</p>
        <pre><code>TELEGRAM_TOKEN = ""        # Your Telegram Bot API token
RAGFLOW_API_KEY = ""       # Your Swipies AI (RAGFlow) API Key
CHAT_ID = ""               # Optional (not used in this script)

# Also update the authorization header:
"Authorization": "Bearer &lt;your-ragflow-key&gt;"
</code></pre>
      </section>

      <section class="card">
        <h2>üöÄ How It Works</h2>
        <ol class="muted">
          <li>User writes a message to the bot.</li>
          <li>The bot sends the message to the Swipies API endpoint:<br><code>POST https://api.swipies.app/api/v1/chats_openai/&lt;chat_id&gt;/chat/completions</code></li>
          <li>Swipies returns streaming chunks like <code>data:{...JSON...}</code> and <code>data:[DONE]</code>.</li>
          <li>The script parses and reconstructs the final answer.</li>
          <li>The bot replies to the user with the generated output.</li>
        </ol>
      </section>

      <section class="card">
        <h2>‚ñ∂Ô∏è Run the Bot</h2>
        <p class="muted">Start the bot with Python:</p>
        <pre><code>python main.py</code></pre>
        <p class="small">If the token is correct, the bot will start polling Telegram.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="card">
        <h2>üß† Core Function</h2>
        <p class="muted">The main helper sends the prompt to Swipies AI and returns final text:</p>
        <pre><code>async def swipies_request(text: str) -&gt; str:
    # sends prompt and parses streaming response
</code></pre>
      </section>

      <section class="card">
        <h2>üì¨ Example Interaction</h2>
        <p class="muted"><strong>User:</strong> Hello, what can you do?</p>
        <p class="muted"><strong>Bot:</strong> I am Swipies AI assistant, ready to help you‚Ä¶</p>
      </section>

      <section class="card">
        <h2>‚ö†Ô∏è Notes</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Replace hard-coded API keys with environment variables for production.</li>
          <li>This version does <strong>not</strong> stream partial responses to Telegram ‚Äî it only sends the final text.</li>
          <li>Verify your Swipies AI chat ID and model name are valid.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="card">
        <h2>üìÑ License</h2>
        <p class="muted">This project is free to use and modify.</p>
      </section>

    </main>

